XORT version 0.01
=================

The README is used to introduce the module and provide instructions on
how to install the module, any machine dependencies it may have (for
example C compilers and installed libraries) and any other information
that should be provided before the module is installed.

A README file is required for CPAN modules since CPAN extracts the
README file from a module distribution so that people browsing the
archive can use it get an idea of the modules uses. It is usually a
good idea to provide version information here so that people can
decide whether fixes for the module are worth downloading.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:
  type perl Makefile.PL for how to configure the parameter for Makefile.PL

   perl Makefile.PL 
   make
   make install
   make clean

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

  XML::DOM
  XML::Parsers::PerlSAX

For more detail instruction, please refere to doc/readme_xort

changes since version 0.006
1.Dumper: filter out all columns which have white spaces ONLY
2.DumperSpec: improve the way to parse <or></or> elements, so only pickup once

changes since version 0.005
1. use placeholder for some repeated DBI calls
2. change the structure to printout XML right after its retrival from database for each individual object, instead of waiting for finishing of complete object. This should use less memory
3. filter out unless column before try to retrieve it from database, for instance, featureprop.feature_id if featureprop is nested within feature.
4. add attribute 'limit', which limit the rows to be selected.
5. make _sql iligitimate element at any place

changes since version 0.004
1. use entity declaration for some FlyBase specific Greek characters. 
   Dump out data in UTF-8, with three option -e for non-ASCII stored in database
   0(default): exactly same format as in database, say raw data->raw data, entity name->entity name
   1: converted all FlyBase defined non-ANSCII into entity names (with entity dec in UTF-8)
   2: converted all FlyBase defined non-ANSCII into PLAIN TEXT

2. debug 99% of -w warning message

3. deal with "distinct on", "group by", "ordered by" in _sql query

4. fix 'loss of space' bug in loader

5. add -y for loader/dumper so it can use user-defined ddl (default in conf/ddl.properties)

6. <name null="true"/> to represent EXPLICIT null value( for loader)

7. fix bug for some regular expression
     <name test="ns">\-(P[A-Z]|XP)$</name>

8 adopt Josh code for xort_dump.pl (Getopt::Long instead of Getopt:Std)





